  "text": "FAPB4 may play a role in pre-eclampsia development. Shangguan and colleagues [CITATION_1] reported increased third trimester FAPB4 levels in women with preeclampsia compared with healthy pregnant and non-pregnant women, suggesting no effect of pregnancy on FABP4, thus implicating FABP4 in pre-eclampsia development.",
